  "prompt": "How did Harry's get its name?",
  "response": "The shave company Harry's got its name as an evocative choice that reflects simplicity, approachability, and a personal touch. Founders Andy Katz-Mayfield and Jeff Raider wanted to create a brand that was genuine and straightforward, and they felt \"Harry's\" conveyed the familiarity and friendliness they envisioned for their line of shaving products. The name is meant to be easy to remember and to symbolize a modern, yet timeless solution for high-quality grooming.",
